    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My apologies for the confusion. Let's get straight to the point. An escrow account in the context of buying a condo in Toronto is a secure financial account managed by a neutral third party, often a title company or an attorney. This account holds the money you pay for the condo, such as your down payment and closing costs, until all the conditions of the sale are met.\n\nThe escrow agent ensures that the seller has the right to sell the property and that there are no legal issues with the title. Once the sale is finalized, the escrow agent releases the funds to the seller. This process protects both you and the seller, ensuring that the money is only released when all the necessary paperwork is completed and the property is legally transferred to you. It's a way to guarantee that the transaction is fair and that both parties fulfill their obligations before the funds change hands. I hope this clarifies the purpose and function of an escrow account for you.",
